34:40.780 --> 34:42.657
-No, no, no, no no, go
ahead, call her back.

34:42.660 --> 34:44.127
Don't let me interrupt.

34:44.130 --> 34:44.824
-Clark!

34:50.950 --> 34:52.087
Clark, I'm sorry.

34:52.090 --> 34:53.717
-I can't hear you,
the water's running.

34:53.720 --> 34:55.972
-I said I'm sorry.

34:55.980 --> 34:57.675
I won't do it anymore.

34:57.680 --> 34:59.739
I won't call her while
you're here, I promise.

34:59.750 --> 35:02.514
-Did you wash your hair
in the kitchen sink?

35:02.520 --> 35:04.568
-Well, I guess so.

35:04.570 --> 35:05.798
I always do.

35:05.800 --> 35:08.166
-Well, in the future,
could you not?

35:08.170 --> 35:10.616
Either that, or could you
clean up all these hairs?

35:10.620 --> 35:11.564
-They're my hairs.

35:11.570 --> 35:12.468
You should love me enough--

35:12.470 --> 35:14.028
-You should love me enough
to change something,

35:14.030 --> 35:15.702
if I want it changed.

35:15.710 --> 35:16.404
-Oh my god.

35:16.410 --> 35:17.877
What's gotten into you?

35:17.880 --> 35:18.574
-Oh!

35:18.580 --> 35:22.550
I'm sorry, I just want some
things different around here.

35:22.560 --> 35:24.232
I never get asked what I want.

35:24.240 --> 35:26.435
-How can I ask you anything,
I can't ever find you.

35:26.440 --> 35:28.647
-Find me when I'm here, damn it!

35:28.650 --> 35:32.108
Talk to me, instead of getting
on the phone with your mother.

35:32.110 --> 35:33.065
-You know what I think?

35:33.070 --> 35:35.971
I think that you just want
to leave, like you always do.

35:35.980 --> 35:37.834
I think you got what you
wanted this morning, and now--

35:37.840 --> 35:40.559
-Do not pretend you didn't want
that just as much as I did.

35:40.560 --> 35:42.414
-No, you know what
I wanted Clark.

35:42.420 --> 35:44.843
I wanted a long lazy
romantic morning like the one

35:44.850 --> 35:46.215
that you promised me.

35:46.220 --> 35:46.914
But guess what?

35:46.920 --> 35:48.387
You know, I don't think
I want that anymore.

35:48.390 --> 35:49.084
-Oh, honey.

35:49.090 --> 35:49.920
-Don't honey me.

35:49.930 --> 35:50.862
You know what?

35:50.870 --> 35:51.620
Just go!

35:51.630 --> 35:52.324
Go!

35:52.330 --> 35:55.208
Off to work, dot of
nine, like usual.

35:55.210 --> 35:57.041
Like the time-card
punching, never-around,

35:57.050 --> 35:58.392
pencil-pusher that you are.

36:01.070 --> 36:03.504
-I'm going.

36:03.510 --> 36:05.558
-So go.

36:13.500 --> 36:15.320
-I signalled I didn't
have the files yet.

36:15.330 --> 36:16.445
What are we doing here?

36:16.450 --> 36:18.668
-I know you don't want to
hear this from me, Elizabeth.

36:18.680 --> 36:20.898
But it only takes three
minutes in the car

36:20.900 --> 36:23.573
to know that you
came back to soon.

36:23.580 --> 36:25.229
Bradley Mullin you can
handle in your sleep,

36:25.230 --> 36:28.700
but Andrew Larrick is
waiting around the corner,

36:28.710 --> 36:30.780
and if you're not
ready for him--

36:30.790 --> 36:31.950
-I'll be ready.

36:31.960 --> 36:34.360
-Of course you feel that way.

36:34.370 --> 36:35.655
But I'm telling
you, I see something

36:35.660 --> 36:38.242
that you're not aware of.

36:38.250 --> 36:40.150
You're afraid.

36:40.160 --> 36:41.582
Too afraid.

36:41.590 --> 36:43.808
You're back, but
you're not back.

36:43.810 --> 36:45.892
-I really do think you're
trying to help, Claudia,

36:45.900 --> 36:47.470
but it just takes
three minutes in a car

36:47.480 --> 36:50.119
to know there's something
else going on with you too,

36:50.120 --> 36:51.473
and I want to know what it is.

36:57.470 --> 36:59.950
-I don't want to
lose anyone else.

37:17.800 --> 37:18.494
-Oh!

37:18.500 --> 37:20.525
This is so, so great of you.

37:20.530 --> 37:23.909
_ I can't believe--
is something wrong?

37:23.910 --> 37:24.990
-I don't have the files.

37:27.500 --> 37:28.444
-I don't understand.

37:28.450 --> 37:29.144
1--

37:29.150 --> 37:32.608
-Every time I went to do
it, guys kept looking at me.

37:32.610 --> 37:35.579
